The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for predicting epileptic seizures using EEG signals. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and cybernetics (cs.CY). Given the focus on machine learning techniques, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of EEG signals and the focus on healthcare applications may also make cs.NE and cs.HC relevant. Finally, the discussion of potential pitfalls and future directions suggests a broader cybernetics perspective, making cs.CY a possible sub-category as well.
